<p>Hi Emil,</p>
<img src="https://carbon-media.accelerator.net/00000000001/eLCmSFooXCddR1qtR6uuPD;760x540.png?auto=webp" width="960" height="463" style="max-width:100%;height:auto;"/>
<p>This is a fresh start. You have a clean, new mind to fill with things that make you happy or inspire you.</p>
<p><strong>Forget how it all worked before.</strong></p>
<p>You don’t have to curate anything at this point. You don’t need to fill up your mind right away either. There’s no pressure to rush this or do it “right.” Just slowly use your mind as you think of it.</p>
<p>💡 Start an article you don’t have time to finish now? Save it to your mind to read later.</p>
<p>💡 See a beautiful image online that inspires you? In your mind.</p>
<p>💡 Read a quote in an email you want to remember? Highlight and save it to your mind.</p>
<img src="https://carbon-media.accelerator.net/00000000001/0IFs1Lz0nXectGfTGYOfHb;760x540.png?auto=webp" width="960" height="463" style="max-width:100%;height:auto;"/>
<p>Slowly but surely, you’ll build a beautiful space filled with things that make you happy, inspired, calmer or more focused.</p>
<p>But don’t rush it or overthink it. Take your time. Your mind is ready when you are.</p>
